Billionaire Fund Manager Cohen Bids for Mets Stake, WSJ Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-04-13T05:46:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/billionaire-fund-manager-cohen-bids-for-mets-stake-wsj-says.html
U.S. hedge fund billionaire  Steve
Cohen  is bidding for a minority stake in the New York Mets
baseball team, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people
familiar with the matter.  Cohen, a long-time Mets fan, is worth $7.3 billion,
according to Forbes magazine, and through his SAC Capital
Advisors LLC manages about $12 billion in assets; the Mets are
tring to raise $200 million to pay down debt and cover losses,
the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
